This branch exists to prevent the "local" branch from being accidentally
pushed to the remote repository.

This orphan branch has no shared history with the rest of the repo. Because
of this, any attempt to `git push` a normal "local" branch (based on master)
will fail with a non-fast-forward error, since the histories are unrelated.

DO NOT delete this remote branch unless you want to allow pushing "local".

== How this was set up ==

From the repository where you want to protect a branch named "local":

    # 1. Create a temporary orphan branch (no history, no files)
    git checkout --orphan local-placeholder
    git rm -rf .

    # 2. Add this marker file and commit
    #    (create DISABLED_BRANCH with explanatory content)
    git add DISABLED_BRANCH
    git commit -m "placeholder: prevent accidental push of local branch"

    # 3. Push the orphan branch to the remote as "local"
    git push origin local-placeholder:local
    #    Use --force if a remote "local" branch already exists:
    #    git push --force origin local-placeholder:local

    # 4. Switch back to your working branch and delete the temp branch
    git checkout local   # or master, or any other branch
    git branch -D local-placeholder

To replicate this for a different branch name, replace "local" and
"local-placeholder" with the appropriate names throughout.
